summary: Male Aeterna preset for use in enderal. (Might also work on skyrim's altmers?)
descriptionHtml:
So, ethereal elven overhaul doesn't work with my Enderal, not sure if it's just me or it doesn't work for everyone. (If it's just me someone please tell me how you got it working xD)
I wanted to play an Aeterna my first playthrough but I can't do Skyrim's 'vanilla' elves, so I went with a Arazealean but on the second playthrough I decided to suck it up and try to make a way [url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lEhfX4AjE3o]'too elfy'[/url] elf. So I used [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/30/?]No More Blocky Faces[/url] to try to smooth it out a bit, which kinda worked.
I managed to get him to a point where I wouldn't mind looking at him for another playthrough

Required stuff
[list]
[*][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/29624/?]Racemenu[/url]
[*][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/68311/?]KS Hairdos[/url]
[*][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/30/?]No More Blocky Faces[/url]
[/list]
Recommended stuff:
[list]
[*][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/43899/]Runic Eyes[/url]
[*][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/73605/?]Ixum's Tattoo's[/url]
[*][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/29977/]XCE Warpaint and Dirt[/url]
[/list]That's about it
author: HellbentHades
